                       "message":  "W08-CANONICAL-MENU-SOURCE: move default editor menu into editor-ui + add Shortcut-\u003eCommand resolver\n\nFirst carve of the accelerator-execution thread (design pass W08.1). Establishes\neditor-ui as the single source of truth for the editor\u0027s four main menus and\nwakes the dormant AcceleratorTable for execution — ZERO behaviour change, no\neditor-shell touch.\n\n- editor-ui: NEW menus/default_menu.rs — pub default_editor_menu() -\u003e MenuRegistry\n  (File/Edit/Play/View extension points + entries + File/Edit accelerators, moved\n  verbatim from the host) + four pub *_menu_point() accessors. Both consumers now\n  build from one definition without a reverse crate edge (host for display today;\n  editor-shell for accelerator execution in W08.2+).\n- editor-ui: ResolveResult::command_for_shortcut(\u0026Shortcut) -\u003e Option\u003c\u0026Command\u003e\n  bridges the O(1) AcceleratorTable (Shortcut-\u003eEntryId) with by_point\n  (EntryId-\u003eCommand). Winner = first-registered (matches AcceleratorTable::resolve);\n  unbound -\u003e None. This is the substrate editor-shell consumes next.\n- editor-egui-host: build_main_menu_entries now resolves default_editor_menu() and\n  projects to the host\u0027s (label, Option\u003cdisplay\u003e, Command) triples; the four local\n  consts are gone. play_item_enabled / menu_item untouched. Display output is\n  byte-identical — the 24 menu_tests display-string pins stay green.\n\nTests (editor-ui): the five shared accelerators (Ctrl+O/S/Shift+S/Z/Y) resolve to\nOpenFile/Save/SaveAs/Undo/Redo via command_for_shortcut; the canonical menu has\nzero conflicts and binds exactly five; declaration order File/Edit/Play/View;\nPlay/View carry no accelerator; resolver winner-under-conflict + miss-returns-None.\n\nNo editor-shell change, no Cargo/edge change, no Command-variant change. The live\nkeystroke cutover + shell parity test are deferred to W08.2/W08.3. Gate: VERIFY OK\n7/7 + 10/10 arch lints; editor-ui 35 menus tests + editor-egui-host 24 menu_tests\ngreen.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
