                       "message":  "W08-CANONICAL-MENU-SOURCE: fix command_for_shortcut under duplicate cross-point ids + refresh menu-bar arc doc\n\nAddresses the two Codex review findings on #308.\n\n(1) BLOCKING — command_for_shortcut could return the wrong Command. It resolved a\nshortcut to a bare EntryId via the accelerator table, then scanned by_point (a\nHashMap) for an entry with that id. EntryId is unique only WITHIN an extension\npoint, so a duplicate id across points let the scan match the wrong point\u0027s entry,\nnondeterministically (HashMap iteration order). Fix: MenuRegistry::resolve now\nbuilds a deterministic Shortcut-\u003eCommand index (point declaration x registration\norder; first registration wins, matching AcceleratorTable::resolve\u0027s winner), and\ncommand_for_shortcut is a direct O(1) lookup into it — no id-scan, correct even\nwhen entry ids repeat across points. Adds regression test\ncommand_for_shortcut_disambiguates_duplicate_ids_across_points (same EntryId in\ntwo extension points, different shortcuts+commands -\u003e each keystroke resolves to\nits own command). Today\u0027s canonical menu has globally-unique ids so behaviour is\nunchanged; the fix hardens the generic helper for plugin-registered entries.\n\n(2) Doc — the editor-egui-host crate-root MENU-BAR ARC ledger said menu\nconstruction lives in the private host `menu` submodule. #308 moved the canonical\nDEFINITION to rge_editor_ui::menus::default_menu; the host submodule now only\nPROJECTS it. Refreshed the entry (adds the #308 canonical-source move) so the\nledger names editor-ui as the definition owner.\n\nNo behaviour change (the host menu_tests display pins stay green); editor-ui 36\nmenus tests pass. Gate: VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
